ice` is true due to the Memory class, the `UnsafeUtil.determineAndroidSupportByAddressSize` call on line 355 will be looking for static methods when it actually returns instance methods.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_UajVDCD4zmDASxKO3dqMpqNi|fc_02cb8d4e695670b70169f7d9709a808194815c9377dca67627\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"javap -classpath /home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.9.0-M2/82942ab9ea2263e25fc62c7ef549f662100d2912/akka-protobuf-v3_3-2.9.0-M2.jar -p 'akka.protobufv3.internal.UnsafeUtil$MemoryAccessor' | head -100 && javap -classpath /home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.9.0-M2/82942ab9ea2263e25fc62c7ef549f662100d2912/akka-protobuf-v3_3-2.9.0-M2.jar -p 'akka.protobufv3.internal.UnsafeUtil$Android64MemoryAccessor' | head -100\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1143, \"output\": 940, \"cacheRead\": 68608, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 70691, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777850723429, \"responseId\": \"resp_02cb8d4e695670b70169f7d96400388194b41c11c6c34a100f\"}}\n46858:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating coding issues**\\n\\nI’m considering if there’s a line length issue with an error on line 69. I might need to make sure the code has type annotations everywhere while keeping documentation minimal. Since this is a test file, having the `Memory` package in the same file seems okay, but I wonder if JUnit might discover it incorrectly. I’m also thinking about potential issues with `final class Memory` being in the wrong package, especially regarding native image paths for protobuf runtime.\\n\\n**Assessing Scala method compilation**\\n\\nI’m wondering if Scala can compile methods with the same name but different overloads for `Long` and `Int`; seems like the JVM signatures should be fine. I also have concerns about `getClass.getClassLoader` returning the right results in a native image, as it may be null. If `Class.forName` could also yield null, that seems problematic. Additionally, I'm considering moving the `Memory` helper into its own file, but maybe it’s best to keep it where it is. I need to ensure my comments remain concise, especially regarding untracked metadata.\\n\\n**Examining git and metadata**\\n\\nI’m considering whether using `git diff --stat` includes untracked files, but I think it doesn't. The final output should definitely highlight changes. I wonder if we need to check the relevance of untracked metadata, since it might come from a generated baseline—but maybe it’s best not to touch it. Another concern is that if `Android.isOnAndroidDevice` is true due to the Memory class, the `UnsafeUtil.determineAndroidSupportByAddressSize` call on line 355 will be looking for static methods when it actually returns instance methods.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_02cb8d4e695670b70169f7d966537c8194abc8090b8d4e35c1\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp99lwn8bTAlOcViqy_HNDiamnPx4UdPw_36649yr_-b-D18bl4SfL5czHYRNPnu2aRtFZFzMLuW4Nx-MTtTUCTPf8ISzBV5HJTBgRJOSGYt0pdGWSiCwq_pZM70ioUFMNfyWCCHwmme6ugTuxuM_Ki6Sk2UgSRGv9RC5yL_uYyKqZ2UQnmXskYUw1hD5dxlxO7V_7e0Koa2kkhwA-TMx1tfsWYh_xIjQQt1IjIuysvvhyIF1PIRG1y9Znt36ubdRGZ_q7QPSLY8bk5ItsmOzdavuO1ejsLDL4CcPPrW5Mw10ZKnKnW1vVuA4FHUU_omwTronBM-aAWmG-_REqM1LtSviZXFlbwpLawZzCmBW__TV81p4sLfNdLKue33t2toAMdh63agrfZqvMBfdF8vnqvUQ36IzM1LTea9YIc-fny6q0JD-z7bs5UjJ8Kbq7QbuuiDLHDHgLvkMSfp5cK_LNl0j4uhn3lwHHeNn1k__mzLAA7eu2MhWSHaTf6J2NHkPcAnyFvRGCTbw6cFUW85Ysbfh3T2xtzL9H_YuLuuPBgZ1ubRJBAlczSI7U6RHni9AKZes0tMYHLmwcIIUZ0a08WPS1ADGyxQmbSZEvKW3wFY2wj8E57AUyV4PNtVsYM0ZdbcN0z438eiuKGyq_SfnLr6IfxIazanV3wUIe-MNSoHWrscOrJHiPIoS9lj_lsa